Gunmen have attacked 18-seater passenger bus, killing two persons in Kwara State. The gunmen abducted an unspecified number of other passengers. The incident happened on June 4 on Obbo-Aiyegunle-Osi Road in Ekiti local government area of the state.   Fashola hands over keys to beneficiaries of Kano housing…     NSE, FERMA mark roads in Abuja to lessen crashes     Lalong hailed for assenting to VAPP law   The gunmen were said to have shot into the vehicle, killing  the driver and a woman, it was said. Police spokesman Ajayi Okasanmi said policemen, vigilantes, local hunters and available members of sister agencies were on the scene to rescue the victims. “Bodies of the dead were retrieved and deposited at Carosi Hospital mortuary for autopsy,” said, adding that the state Commissioner of police Tuesday Assayomo had ordered  a manhunt for the perpetrators.